TITLE: Making POST Request with Automatic Unmarshalling in Resty (Go)
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to send a POST request with a JSON body using Resty, automatically unmarshal the response into a result struct, and capture errors into an error struct. Dependencies include the github.com/go-resty/resty/v2 package. The SetResult and SetError methods determine the destination structs for successful and error responses. Inputs are the User struct for credentials and the URL; outputs are populated LoginResponse or LoginError structs. Proper error handling and type assertions are also shown.
SOURCE: https://github.com/go-resty/docs/blob/main/content/docs/response-auto-parse.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
res, err := client.R().
    SetBody(User{
        Username: "testuser",
        Password: "testpass",
    }). // default request content-type is JSON
    SetResult(&LoginResponse{}).
    SetError(&LoginError{}).
    Post("https://myapp.com/login")

fmt.Println(err)
fmt.Println(res.Result().(*LoginResponse))
fmt.Println(res.Error().(*LoginError))
```

