TITLE: Creating Weighted Round Robin Load Balancer in Go
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a Weighted Round Robin load balancer using Resty v3, allowing hosts to be assigned different weights for load distribution. Dependencies include Resty and a recovery duration setting. It requires a list of hosts with corresponding weights, affecting the request percentages. The output is an initialized Resty client with a Weighted Round Robin load balancing strategy.
SOURCE: https://github.com/go-resty/docs/blob/main/content/docs/load-balancer-and-service-discovery.md#2025-04-22_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
// create a load balancer
// accepts one or more Host(s)
wrr, err := resty.NewWeightedRoundRobin(
    3*time.Second, // recovery duration
    []*resty.Host{
        {
            BaseURL: "https://example1.com",
            Weight:  50, // determines the percentage of requests to this host
        },
        {BaseURL: "https://example2.com", Weight: 30},
        {BaseURL: "https://example3.com", Weight: 20},
    }...,
)
if err != nil {
    log.Printf("ERROR %v", err)
    return
}

// by default, the recovery duration is 120 seconds, which can be changed as follows
// wrr.SetRecoveryDuration(3 * time.Minute)

// create Resty client
c := resty.New().
    SetLoadBalancer(wrr)
defer c.Close()

// start using the client ...
```

