DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows consuming multiple SSE event types using Resty's AddEventListener method in Go. It defines a custom UserEvent struct that matches expected event payloads. The EventSource setup includes generic and event-specific listeners for 'user_connect' and 'user_message', all casting the event data appropriately. This approach is useful when an SSE stream provides heterogeneous events, and typed handling is desired. Inputs: JSON SSE data for different event names. Outputs: Printed struct or event representations. Dependencies: Resty v3 with EventSource, time package, fmt package.
