TITLE: Retrieving Redirect History with Go-Resty
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates how to use the RedirectHistory method in Resty v3 to access information about redirects that occurred during an HTTP request. It creates a new Resty client, makes a GET request, and then iterates through the redirect history, printing the status code and URL for each redirect.
SOURCE: https://github.com/go-resty/docs/blob/main/content/docs/example/redirect-history.md#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: go
CODE:
```
package main

import (
	"fmt"

	"resty.dev/v3"
)

func main() {
	c := resty.New()
	defer c.Close()

	res, _ := c.R().Get("http://resty.dev")

	for _, rh := range res.RedirectHistory() {
		fmt.Println(rh.StatusCode, rh.URL)
	}
}
```
